  "body": "***Type***: Bug\r\n***Summary***: Expandable views with the list of options above the message box flickers by the height.\r\nThe next expandable views affected for instance:\r\n- Console -> /faucet -> observe \"animated\" suggested url option view\r\n- Group Chat -> /request -> observe \"animated\" list of contacts view\r\n- Group Chat -> /send -> observe \"animated\" list of contacts view\r\n\r\nSee on video the based on /debug's 'On' and 'Off' options: \r\nhttps://drive.google.com/open?id=1AMcESD4H41xCzfrSaHiPcM3zkMMKckwJ\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nNon flickering expandable views \r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nFlickering expandable views with the list of options on Android\r\n\r\n### To reproduce:\r\n1) Open Status\r\n2) Navigate to Console screen\r\n3) Tap `[/]` button in the message input box (/faucet and /debug suggested options appeared)\r\n4) Tap `debug` option\r\n5) Observe if expanded view with 'On' and 'Off' options continuously jumping up and down on 1px.\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: 0.9.10-720-g64b24826+ \r\n* Operating System: confirmed on Android 7.0 (Samsung J7 real device), Android 8.0.0 on OnePlus 5 (real device)\r\n\r\n### Additional Information 2\r\nIt's not present on iOS. \r\nAlso confirmed that issue is **not visible** on Samsung Galaxy S8 with Android 7.\r\nAnd I could not reproduce it on Android emulators.\r\n\r\nLikely it was introduced with the https://github.com/status-im/status-react/pull/3405 : I didn't see this issue on 253rd nightly develop.",
